cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is primarily focused on information retrieval (IR) and proposes a method to transfer a retrieval system trained on English collections to non-English queries and documents using pre-trained multilingual language models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The paper also leverages pre-trained language models, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely sub-category. 

The proposed approach involves transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves the use of multilingual data, which falls under the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (CVPR). Therefore, cs.CY (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
